  "prompt": "What are some examples of red meat? How does it differ from white meat?",
  "response": "Red meat typically refers to meat from mammals, while white meat comes from poultry and fish. Here are some examples:\n\nRed Meat Examples:\n1. Beef\n2. Lamb\n3. Pork\n4. Goat\n5. Veal\n6. Venison (deer meat)\n\nDifferences between Red and White Meat:\n\nRed Meat:\n- Higher in myoglobin (gives meat red color)\n- More saturated fat\n- Higher iron content\n- Generally more calories\n- Often associated with higher health risks when consumed in excess\n\nWhite Meat:\n- Lower in myoglobin\n- Less saturated fat\n- Lower calorie content\n- Lower iron content\n- Generally considered healthier option\n- Examples include:\n  - Chicken\n  - Turkey\n  - Fish\n  - Some types of seafood\n\nNutritional recommendations often suggest limiting red meat consumption and choosing white meat more frequently for a balanced diet.",
